Axiom, conversion and weakening rules:


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (ax$_x$)}
        \RightLabel {\small {$(x : \phi ) \in  \Gamma , \mathcal {H} \vdash  \Gamma $}}
        \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \phi $}
      \end {bprooftree}
      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \phi $}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (conv)}
        \RightLabel {\small {$\phi  =_\beta  \psi  , \mathcal {H} \vdash  \psi $}}
        \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \psi $}
      \end {bprooftree}






    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \psi $}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (wk$_x$)}
        \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  , x : \phi  \vdash  \psi $}
      \end {bprooftree}




    Logical fragment:


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  , x : \phi  \vdash  \psi $}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (imp-intro$_x$)}
        \RightLabel {\small {$x \notin  \text {lbl}(\Gamma )$}}
        \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \phi  \Rightarrow  \psi $}
      \end {bprooftree}
      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \phi  \Rightarrow  \psi $}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \phi $}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (impl-elim)}
        \BinaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \psi $}
      \end {bprooftree}






    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H}, x^\star  : T ; \Gamma  \vdash  \phi $}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (forall-intro)}
        \RightLabel {\small {$x \notin  \text {fv}(\Gamma )$}}
        \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \forall (x : T).\phi $}
      \end {bprooftree}
      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \forall (x : T).\phi $}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (forall-elim)}
        \RightLabel {\small {$\mathcal {H} \vdash  t : T$}}
        \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \phi [t/x]$}
      \end {bprooftree}




    Fixed point rules:


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  (\mu ^\alpha  (x : T). \phi )\ \vec {\psi }$}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  , x : \exists \beta  < \alpha . \phi [\mu ^\beta  (x : T). \phi  / x]\ \vec {\psi } \vdash  \chi $}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (unfold$_x$)}
        \RightLabel {\small {$\beta  \notin  \text {fv}(\phi  , \vec {\psi }) \cup  \{\alpha \} , x \notin  \text {lbl}(\Gamma )$}}
        \BinaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \chi $}
      \end {bprooftree}






    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \exists \beta  < \alpha . \phi [\mu ^\beta  (x : T). \phi  / x]\ \vec {\psi }$}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (fold)}
        \RightLabel {\small {$\beta  \notin  \text {fv}(\phi  , \vec {\psi }) \cup  \{\alpha \}$}}
        \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  (\mu ^\alpha  (x : T). \phi )\ \vec {\psi }$}
      \end {bprooftree}




    Ordinal rules:


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (ord-next)}
        \RightLabel {\small {$\mathcal {H} \vdash  \Gamma $}}
        \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \exists \beta .\alpha  < \beta $}
      \end {bprooftree}
      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \alpha  < \gamma $}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \gamma  < \beta $}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (ord-trans)}
        \BinaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \alpha  < \beta $}
      \end {bprooftree}






    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (ord-irrefl$_x$)}
        \RightLabel {\small {$\mathcal {H} \vdash  \Gamma $}}
        \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma , x : \alpha  < \alpha  \vdash  \bot $}
      \end {bprooftree}
      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \phi $}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (ord-intro)}
        \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \exists  \alpha . \phi $}
      \end {bprooftree}






    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

      \begin {bprooftree}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \exists  \alpha . \phi $}
        \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  , x : \phi  \vdash  \psi $}
        \LeftLabel {\small  (ord-elim$_x$)}
        \RightLabel {\small {$\alpha  \notin  \text {fv}(\psi ), x \notin  \text {lbl}(\Gamma )$}}
        \BinaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \psi $}
      \end {bprooftree}

Let:

\Sigma  be a proof of \mathcal {H} ; \Gamma , x : \phi  \vdash  \psi 

\Pi  be a proof of \mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \phi  
    We define the notation \Sigma [\Pi  / x]


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

In trying to define reudctions in the new system with weakening, it turns out that we have a problem. The issue arises when you consdier \Rightarrow -reduction in a particular case. We ideally want the tree:


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

    \begin {bprooftree}
      \AxiomC {$\Sigma $}
      \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  , x : \phi  \vdash  \psi $}
      \LeftLabel {\small  (wk$_y$)}
      \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  , y : \chi , x : \phi  \vdash  \psi $}
      \LeftLabel {\small  (imp-intro$_x$)}
      \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma , y : \chi  \vdash  \phi  \Rightarrow  \psi $}

      \AxiomC {$\Pi $}
      \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma , y : \chi  \vdash  \phi $}

      \BinaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma , y : \chi  \vdash  \psi $}
    \end {bprooftree}


  to reduce to something like:


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

    \begin {bprooftree}
      \AxiomC {$\Sigma [\Pi  / x]$}
      \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma , y : \chi  \vdash  \psi $}
    \end {bprooftree}


  with some sensible notion of substitution. However, notice that the y : \chi  which is required as a hypothesis in the subproof \Pi  is weakened away. This is problematic: wherever in \Sigma  we have \phi  being derived by an axiom rule, we want to replace it with the proof \Pi , but we cannot since y : \chi  will not be in the context at that axiom.

The solution here is to "push the weakening further up \Sigma ", but this is not always possible. Consider this possible fragment of a cyclic proof (the cycle denoted by *):


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

    \begin {bprooftree}
      \AxiomC {*\ $\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma ' \vdash  \psi '$}
      \UnaryInfC {$\vdots $}
      \UnaryInfC {*\ $\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \psi $}
      \LeftLabel {\small  (wk$_y$)}
      \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma , y : \chi  \vdash  \psi $}
    \end {bprooftree}


  We can only push the weakening past the companion of the cycle if there are no free formulae variables in \chi  that "interact badly" with the induced substitution along the cycle. As in, it could be that for the induced substitution \theta  on formula variables along this cycle, we have \chi  \neq  \theta (\chi ). This would mean that adding y : \chi  to the companion and bud would invalidate the cycle. Call weakingings that don't interact badly with a cycle "good weakenings" for now.

Axiom and conversion rules:


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

    \begin {bprooftree}
      \AxiomC {}
      \LeftLabel {\small  (ax)}
      \RightLabel {\small {$\phi  \in  \Gamma , \mathcal {H} \vdash  \Gamma $}}
      \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \phi $}
    \end {bprooftree}
    \begin {bprooftree}
      \AxiomC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \phi $}
      \LeftLabel {\small  (conv)}
      \RightLabel {\small {$\phi  =_\beta  \psi  , \mathcal {H} \vdash  \psi $}}
      \UnaryInfC {$\mathcal {H} ; \Gamma  \vdash  \psi $}
    \end {bprooftree}




  Logical fragment:


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
